			<title><![CDATA[May '14 Release Thread]]></title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?76753-May-14-Release-Thread&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Thu, 01 May 2014 07:28:34 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>May is looking to be the last big hurrah before summer doldrums kick in. There are a couple of notable titles coming out this month which will likely be the biggest releases until later this year. 
 
The big one is surely *Watch Dogs*. It was originally supposed to come out shortly after GTA 5 last...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>May is looking to be the last big hurrah before summer doldrums kick in. There are a couple of notable titles coming out this month which will likely be the biggest releases until later this year.<br />
<br />
The big one is surely <b>Watch Dogs</b>. It was originally supposed to come out shortly after GTA 5 last year, but Ubisoft delayed it in an effort to expand its content. My expectation is that this will be the difference between Assassin's Creed 1 and 2, between having a prototype and having a fully fledged game. Still, I think some people might be let down due to unrealistic expectations.<br />
<br />
The second most important release this month will arguably be <b>Mario Kart 8</b>. Nintendo is already pushing it pretty hard, no doubt gambling on it improving their position with the Wii U. Mario Kart has long been one of their best selling franchises, appealing to core and casual alike. <br />
<br />
But that's not all, the new <b>Wolfenstein</b> game comes out this month, the PS3 gets action rpg <b>Drakengard 3</b>, and the new game from the makers of Bastion, <b>Transistor</b>, comes out on PC and PS4.<br />
<br />
On the handheld front, this month Sony launches their new Vita model, along with a port of Borderlands 2. The 3DS meanwhile gets a new kirby game and mario golf.<br />
<br />
